table-1584-659.caption: Title history
data: Defeated the Head Bangers and Huracán Castillo Jr. and Savio Vega in a three way dance tournament final.

Commissioner José Estrada ordered Ricky Santana to defend the title. Santana said his tag team partner, Val Venis, was injured. Commissioner named Sean Hill as his partner. The title defense was one between Santana and Hill vs. Perez and Castillo, that ended in a disqualification. A challenge was issued and Fidel Sierra was added by the heels and Savio Vega by the faces in a six men match, being a match that if Savio Vega pinned Sean Hill and then Castillo and Pérez won the title. After the babyfaces wins, Castillo and Pérez were crowned tag team champions. Castillo and Pérez then turned on Vega and become heels.
Headhunter II substituted for Steve Bradley when Bradley was called by WWE on June 8, 2000. Bradley later returned from WWE and reassumed the Tag Team Title on June 14, 2000
This change took plave after a 4-Way match between those two teams, Starr Corporation and Sexy and Sensual (Shan Hill and Andrés Borges)
title was held up after a Match vs. Nueva Generación

Ricky Banderas named a new partner, Miguelito Pérez, on August 6 after he turned on Nuevo Gran Apolo. On August 13 any combination of Ricky Banderas, Miguel Pérez, Pain and Huracán Castillo is declared as qualified to defend the title. Fidel Sierra is added at the August 20 show at Lares, PR (but Sierra is no longer with IWA)
Stipulation was that if Perez and Apolo lose they couldn't be a team anymore.
Defeat Nuevo Gran Apolo in a handicap match. Miguel Perez no showed.
D-Lo Brown and Shane defeated Los Boricuas (Perez and Castillo) and Starr Corporation in a 3 Way Dance Match to win the IWA Tag Team Titles when Hombre Dinamita interfered, sidekicking Chicky Starr.
Defeated Pete Gas and Chaz and the team of Shane and D-Lo Brown in a three way dance match to become the new Tag Team Champions

They wrestled Tiger Ali Singh and Big Russ McCollough on a tag team match but since they were all member of the NEW CORPORATION, they faked the match. Then Savio Ordered the match to be a Title match adding Los Boricuas. At the end Russ was knocked out and then Castillo hit Zaruxx with the bell, Zaruxx landed over Russ and Castillo came to pin both. Savio ruled that since Zaruxx was pinning Russ, Zaruxx and Bruno won the Tag Team Titles.
Defeated Pain and Angel (substituting for Tiger Ali Singh)
Shane no showed under a deportation stipulation (in reality he was headed to Japan)

Miguel Perez defeated Huracán Castillo in a No DQ match to win control of the tag team titles at the Antio Barcelo Coliseum on 09/21/2002 at Toa Baja, PR. Perez picked Savio Vega to be his new tag team partner.
Savio Vega vacated the IWA Tag Team Title due after for failure to defend the title for 30 days due to Eric Alexander being injured.

In a match between former tag team partners, Abyss (1/2 of the Tag Team of the promotion) defeated Miguel Perez (1/2 of the tag team) to win the total control of the title, after Shane interfered. Abyss handed him the other belt, so new tag team champions are Shane and Abyss.
Defeated Miguelito Perez and Slash Venom to win the vacant titles.
Defeated the teams of Los Illegales, La Compañía (Victor the Bodyguard and Chet Jabronski) and Los Boricuas.
Defeated Thunder & Lightning in a cage match
Thunder suffered an injury on 1/6/2005 and Savio Vega named Anarchy Lightning's partner and co-holder of the titles
Title suspended after match w/ Diabolico & Draco Lee and Noriega & Golden Boy.
Defeated Noriega & Golden Boy for held-up title.
Los Arabes defeated in Fatal Four Way Match a Chicano & Bryan Madness, Noel Rodríguez & Richard Rondón and Chris Joel & Golden Boy.
